Global Funds Buy Net 8.12 billion Rupees of Indian Derivatives

-- B y   P a r e s h   J a t a k i a
-- 
2011-03-23T03:32:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-23/global-funds-buy-net-8-12-billion-rupees-of-indian-derivatives.html
Global funds bought a net 8.12
billion rupees ($181 million) of Indian equity  derivatives 
yesterday, according to the National Stock Exchange.  Open interest, or the number of contracts outstanding in
value terms, gained 0.3 percent to 928.9 billion rupees, or 32.4
percent of the gross market position, according to the
exchangeâ€™s website. Open interest reached a record 1.6 trillion
rupees on Sept. 21.  Foreign investors bought a net 2.4 billion rupees of shares
in the  cash  segment yesterday, according to preliminary data
given by the bourse.  To contact the reporter on this story:
